body:
My preference would be to parse it as a union type, then separately check each type in the union type. I don't believe phpdocumentor supports it, but I don't think it was explicitly forbidden.

Aside: This is much less common than I thought.

```
zend_all/vendor/zendframework/zend-mail/src/Protocol/Smtp.php
239:     * @throws \Exception|Exception\ExceptionInterface

zend_all/vendor/zendframework/zend-stratigility/src/Next.php
412:     * @throws Throwable|\Exception
```



```php
<?php

/**
 * Unexpected UndefinedDocblockClass Docblock-defined class or interface RuntimeException|TypeError does not exist
 * @throws RuntimeException|TypeError
 */
function test() {
}
```

Something along these lines, but should be done instead by parsing the union type, iterating over the values, and warning about non-objects such as `int`

```patch
--- a/src/Psalm/Internal/Visitor/ReflectorVisitor.php
+++ b/src/Psalm/Internal/Visitor/ReflectorVisitor.php
@@ -2035,16 +2035,18 @@ class ReflectorVisitor extends PhpParser\NodeVisitorAbstract implements PhpParse
 
         $storage->suppressed_issues = $docblock_info->suppress;
 
-        foreach ($docblock_info->throws as $throw_class) {
-            $exception_fqcln = Type::getFQCLNFromString(
-                $throw_class,
-                $this->aliases
-            );
+        foreach ($docblock_info->throws as $throw_union_type) {
+            foreach (array_map('trim', explode('|', $throw_union_type)) as $throw_class) {
+                $exception_fqcln = Type::getFQCLNFromString(
+                    $throw_class,
+                    $this->aliases
+                );
 
-            $this->codebase->scanner->queueClassLikeForScanning($exception_fqcln, $this->file_path);
-            $this->file_storage->referenced_classlikes[strtolower($exception_fqcln)] = $exception_fqcln;
+                $this->codebase->scanner->queueClassLikeForScanning($exception_fqcln, $this->file_path);
+                $this->file_storage->referenced_classlikes[strtolower($exception_fqcln)] = $exception_fqcln;
 
-            $storage->throws[$exception_fqcln] = true;
+                $storage->throws[$exception_fqcln] = true;
+            }
         }
```
